OL,3,CVictims say battle 'half won' on
OL,4,Clegacy as government remains
OL,5,C'committed'
OL,7,FCampaigners behind a legal challenge
OL,8,Fto the government's controversial
OL,9,FLegacy Act have described winning
OL,10,F"half" their case.
OL,12,FMr Justice Colton declared that parts
OL,13,Fof the legislation aimed at dealing
OL,14,Fwith the consequences of the conflict
OL,15,Fin Northern Ireland breach the
OL,16,FEuropean Convention on Human Rights.
OL,18,FSome have called for the act to be
OL,19,Fsuspended in light of the ruling,
OL,20,Fhowever the government say they remain
OL,21,F'committed' to the act.
