OL,7,FA judgment at Belfast High Court on
OL,8,FWednesday ruled that the provision for
OL,9,Fconditional immunity from prosecution
OL,10,Ffor Troubles offences in the Act is
OL,11,Fnot compliant with the European
OL,12,FConvention on Human Rights (ECHR).
OL,13,FHowever, it was also ruled that the
OL,14,FIndependent Commission for
OL,15,FReconciliation and Information
OL,16,FRecovery (ICRIR) ` set up in the Act
OL,17,Fto probe Troubles killings ` could
OL,18,Fcarry out human rights-compliant
OL,19,Finvestigations.JMartina Dillon, John
OL,20,FMcEvoy and Lynda McManus were behind
OL,21,Fthe challenge, questioning the human
OL,22,Frights compliance of the Act, and have
OL,23,Fvowed to fight on, potentially to the
OL,24,FSupreme Court.JA large number of
OL,25,Fsupporters accompanied the trio to
OL,26,Fcourt on Wednesday, and banners
