OL,7,FGrainne Teggart from Amnesty
OL,8,FInternational described an "important
OL,9,Fand significant development in a
OL,10,Fcomplex case".J"We welcome the
OL,11,Ffindings from the court today,
OL,12,Fparticularly in respect of immunity
OL,13,Ffrom prosecutions and striking that
OL,14,Fout of the law and also the findings
OL,15,Faround civil claims, that that
OL,16,Fimmediate ban has also been struck
OL,17,Fout," she said.J"That's an important
OL,18,Fand significant development for many
OL,19,Fvictims. Today was always going to be
OL,20,Fround one, we know this is a complex
OL,21,Fpiece of legislation and a complex
OL,22,Fcase so we will continue to fight on
OL,23,Funtil such times as victims' rights
OL,24,Fare vindicated."JMs Teggart said there
OL,25,Fare "significant questions" for
OL,26,FSecretary of State Chris Heaton-Harris
